==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''calculus'', [[pebble]] (used for counting), diminuitive of ''[[calx]]'', [[limestone]], + diminuitive suffix ''[[-ulus]]''

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''calculus''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''calculi''')

#{{mathematics}} Any formal system in which [[symbolic expression]]s are manipulated according to fixed rules.
#{{analysis}} (''uncountable'') [[differential calculus|Differential calculus]] and [[integral calculus]] considered as a single subject.
#{{medicine}} a stony [[concretion]] that forms in a bodily organ
#:''renal calculus'' ( = [[kidney stone]])
#(''dentistry'') (''uncountable'') deposits of [[calcium phosphate]] salts on teeth

